  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `v1.10.1` (have noticed this issue on older versions as well)\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe node should broadcast the pending transactions after overwriting them after a while.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThe node is broadcasting the first few transactions then stop broadcasting the new transactions until we restart it.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behavior\r\n1- Send some transactions (like 200 transactions) from the same account with a very low gas price comparing with the current gas price on the network\r\n2- Update the gas price of these transactions after 2-3 days to speed them\r\n3- The node broadcasts some of the new transactions only then stop broadcasting any other transaction from the same account until we restart the node",
